      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "PORTLAND, Ore, July 31.-Gov-\nernor George III. Chamberlain, State\nTreasurer Moore and Secretary of\nState Dunbar are now in conference\nin Portland relative to the establish\nment of rates for the Portage road.\n1t is regarded as doubtful by the\nstates executives if the tariff will be\ncompleted for several days, but in\nview of the strong desire on the part\nof farmers to be made acquainted\nwith the charges so they may figure\non shipping fall grain ii is regarded\nlikely the wheat rate at least will be\nannounced today. 1t is understood\nprivately that the tariff on this cere-\nal from Lewiston to Portland will be\n50 ton. against Sass charged by the\nrailroads."
    }
